                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./36: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-05T17:00:00-03:00"
                            >September 5, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>303. For the Under Secretary. Your 168, September 4, 6 p.m. Aranha and President
                    Vargas approve agenda as drafted.</p>
                <p>Aranha wants to know who is going from Washington. He would like to go but does
                    not feel that he can leave Rio de Janeiro at this time. He will send several
                    technical experts from here by air. He <pb facs="0026" n="20" xml:id="pg_20"/>
                    has in mind sending his Ambassador at Washington as principal delegate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
